parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the clutch to suddenly release while letting up the pedal, leading to the vehicle lurching forward or backward, which can cause accidents or loss of control.
